  In this work we shall show that the Cauchy problem \begin{equation} \left\{
\begin{aligned} &(u_t+u^pu_x+\mathcal H\partial_x^2u+ \alpha\mathcal
H\partial_y^2u )_x - \gamma u_{yy}=0 \quad p\in{\nat}
  &u(0;x,y)=\phi{(x,y)}
  \end{aligned}
  \right. \end{equation} is locally well-posed in the Sobolev spaces
$H^s({\re}^2)$, $X^s$ and weighted spaces $X_s(w^2)$, for $s>2$.
